The paper deals with the computational complexity of the Max-Cut problem, which is a well-studied problem in computer science. The paper uses techniques from discrete mathematics, computational complexity, and graph theory to prove its results. Therefore, cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), cs.CC (Computational Complexity), and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) are likely categories. The paper also deals with graph theory and optimization, which are covered in cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), respectively.
